spanGrp.span: This is the story of how we just came
gole mwee selselaen ne mwiir be nge mirim bwiri me
to live in the village in this area
so lan vele ne r gole
we just came to this side (of the island)
mirim bwiri me tai r gole
were our grandfathers, they lived on the other side of the sea at Fanbak
mwee ememriel tutu yel lar so tai tie Fanbyak
one person, one man, his name is
enten hol , yaalfu hol isan nge
Tok ne Bu, he is ours
Tok ne Bu go mwee gememriel go
They were doing a pig killing ceremnony on the other side of the creek here (Tolatakor, near Faramsu)
lam yene butiri hol nga tai wol le
Tok ne Bu came into this ceremony
Tok ne Bu meme lon ruen gola
a ceremony for the high ranking men
ruen ne yaalfu , ruen san yaalfu yel
he came and called a woman of that place (choose a wife)
meme mwike ven , ven hol nr gola
he called for a woman called
Tuwu, that woman was already with someone
Tuwu , ven gola tutu saale enten hol bur
she was with the son of Byal Mweleun
tutu saale lobungbung se Byal Mweleun
like that the two of them lived
go mwiir la lom so van
when the man from Fanbak came, Tok ne Bu just came and called and took that woman
taem go yaalfu te Fyanbyak meme , Tok ne Bu meme nga r me ke kuu ven gola
the two of them returned to Fanbak, and the woman
lom kolili van Fanbyak r ven
a month has passed (since her period)
she was pregnant with a child from this place (Lonbulubyal)
mwelee lobungbung ru bur nr gole
then they went, they went to Fanbak
ale lom bwiri an , lom bwiri an Fanbyak
Tok ne Bu had taken away his daughter-in-law, had called out his daughter-in-law
Tok ne Bu mukurkuu lahan , mwikeku lahan
then he sent a message, he said "that's alright"
ngar mwesengane sol usili , mwi gile , " mue ten nga ru "
"Tok ne Bu has called out there"
" Tok ne Bu mwike ru van la "
"I am sending a message to say"
" ru nam sengane sol usili nga van go gile babean "
"she will go and live there, but the child who is with her"
babean tu la go lobungbung go muru ne nge
you two will put his name as Raulu
o gab lingi isan nge Raulu
"and if it is a woman, you will call her Matee"
" a gile tee ven egab lingi isan nge Matee "
they went and lived in Fanbak then
lom an ru Fanbyak van , ale
she went and gave birth to a child, she went and gave birth and it was a man
enten mean sotiel lobungbung mean sotiel fono mwee man
ngar lim lingi isan nge Raulu
following the idea of Byal Mweleun
as it was his daughter-in-law , Tuwu
go tee lahan tu nge Tuwu gola
he sent a message about that child
he said that child will, they will look after him there, when he is big he will just become a man in this place
mwigile go lobungbung babwe egab kulkul fon la abwee tirbonok abwiri me yaalfu nr gole
looked after Raulu for a long time
kulkul fon Raulu van van van
then they went and sent him back here
o lim an sengan liline me le
OK they just came and did his circumcision payment then
Ale lam bwiri me yene san maalgel nga
he just became a man in this place
mwibwiri me yaalfu nr go ren
he came and killed a pig
the father of Byal Mweleun gave him his name of Bwerang Wawaa
teman go Mal Mweleun mwilingi isan nge Bwerang Wawaa
went and lived with Tok ne Bu, went
mean ru saane Tok ne Bu mean
went and gave birth to Raulu first
Tuwu gave birth to Raulu first
Tuwu mwilingi Raulu mwee m ale
Tok ne Bu, his other child
Tok ne Bu san lobungbung sen
his other child was just born
san lobungbung sen go mn mwibwiri lingi mn
their mother was Tuwu, together with Raulu
their father was Tok ne Bu
alal dadi nge Tok ne Bu
the two of them went, they stayed in Fanbak now
lom , lom , lom , lom so van , lim so Fyanbyak van ngela o
Raulu had already come to that place (Merongrong)
Raulu bur meme ru nr gole
Raulu he returned and came and stayed there
Raulu mukolili me me ru le
the man (James Tobyul) from that place went and took and came as he came and showed
enten te nr gole mean uri me ben go meme bisene
his ground, where it will be in that place (While he was away Raulu's biological father died and James Tobyul of Chief Job's family showed him his ground)
an tan go abwiri tu nr go ren
it is the area on the other side of the creek, Nolili, Lonrayer
nge r tai wol Nolili , Lonrayer gola
Lonrayer is the ground of his mother
Lonrayer o mwee tan ne lahan
OK when he came and lived there
Ale bone go meme ru le
he came and took a woman
from there, this woman did not bear a child
nr gole , ven gola tolo lingi enten r hol
he came and took a woman who did not give birth to a child
meme uri ven hol r tolo bwiri lingi enten r hol
he returned to the others (in Fanbak)
went and said they should come and live on that ground
mean gile go lib me , lib me so lon tan gole
he returned to the others and took the old people, they came
mukolili vane gilil mean lee tabaa gilil lim me
with their father too, he came
mane aliel dadi go mn r meme
it is Kali (Kali and his family)
Lim me so nr gole van van van van
one is Byungkon, one was Charlie
hol nge Byungkon , hol nge Sarli
saliel sista yel lamwee lon mele
one group went and lived on the other side of the sea (in Konkon, or SE Ambrym)
lenglang hol lam an so tai tie
They came and lived there over there, we came and lived, came
Lim me so le van ngela go gememriel mirim me so mirim me
we too we came and were born
at that time we came and lived
lon taem gola mirim me so
in the hands of the three old men who followed Raulu who is indigenous to this place
lon vela tabaa gilil usili go nga ngenge Raulu mwee ten r gole
he took us and put us
Ale mwe lee gememriel mn mwe lingi gememriel
as he had no children and
their mother with Kali is one (Kali and Raulu have the same mother)
alal mama mane Kali tee hol nga
he made it so that we come
and took the right to his ground, where we live in this place
uri raet ne an tan go mirim so en r go ren
we are still living her in this place today
nge mirim ran so nr go ren lonla gole bwe
our generation is with the children now
sememriel lenglang sie muru lan lobungbung yel mn ngele
They too, their children they came and are growing up
Ale yel mn saal lobungbung yel lam me ru lam mwee tirbobo
and they live on this ground
r mem so nga lon tan go nga ngenge
they took us and came before and came here
nge lor lee gemem me marin go meme so le
we are still lving in this place now
mem ran so nr go ren bwe ngele
the old men, they are finished
Nge isan nge Byungkon mweran ru
we too are becoming old now
ah gememriel mn ru mirim mermar ngele
sememriel lobungbung yel nge lam mwee lon mele
we just live, we just came and lived on this side according to that story
mem so nga, mem bwiri me so tar gole usili saaren gola
the story that I told there
and he came before and we
know that we are indigenous to here according to
kilbwele go mirim mwee ten r gole usili
who is Tuwu who bore Kali, who fathered Raulu
go mwee Tuwu go mwi lingi Kali go mwi lingi Raulu
and made us take the big rights here
r mwiyene mirim uri raet go tobo ru le
a ru mirim me lon mele
sememriel lobungbung man yel , sememriel lobungbung ven yel
it has come to another generation which are still small, who are coming
meme lan lenglang sie go mn go lam kekai mn go ru lam me
and we are still here yet until now
r mirim ran so nga le bwe mosore taem gole
I think the story of us how we came to live here
abwee se selselaen ne gememriel go mirim me so le
our story now of our coming here
sememriel selselaen ngangela go mirim me so nr gole
